Pluty  is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Pieniężno, within Braniewo County, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, in northern Poland. It lies approximately  north-east of Pieniężno,  south-east of Braniewo, and  north of the regional capital Olsztyn.
